relationship with the business person where you are truly working

00:50:43.000 --> 00:50:47.000
together and it's not just okay data scientists go do your

00:50:47.000 --> 00:50:51.000
thing and then come back when you're done, that's when I think the rabbit hole

00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:55.000
problem gets bad. There's a tendency for

00:50:55.000 --> 00:50:59.000
I think both sides to be like well I'm busy in the business

00:50:59.000 --> 00:51:03.000
so you just come back to me later.

00:51:03.000 --> 00:51:07.000
As the data scientist, I think you just cannot

00:51:07.000 --> 00:51:11.000
you can't go for that. I require if I'm doing work with you or for

00:51:11.000 --> 00:51:15.000
you, you have to be my partner. Otherwise

00:51:15.000 --> 00:51:19.000
it's not going to succeed.

00:51:19.000 --> 00:51:23.000
I don't know if that helps you.

00:51:23.000 --> 00:51:27.000
I have noticed people don't spend enough time

00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:31.000
creating that relationship and enforcing that relationship. What was that, sorry?

00:51:31.000 --> 00:51:35.000
That makes total sense.

00:51:35.000 --> 00:51:39.000
I've definitely had experience of putting in

00:51:39.000 --> 00:51:43.000
hours and hours on analysis and then the business is like

00:51:43.000 --> 00:51:47.000
cool, but I don't know if they're using it or

00:51:47.000 --> 00:51:51.000
what exactly is happening with it. It's hard to say if that was even

00:51:51.000 --> 00:51:55.000
worthwhile.

00:51:55.000 --> 00:51:59.000
Sorry, maybe I can jump in. Sorry to interrupt you. What you said before

00:51:59.000 --> 00:52:03.000
about talking with the people in compliance, I think was really

00:52:03.000 --> 00:52:07.000
relevant here also because I think oftentimes it's a communications issue.

00:52:07.000 --> 00:52:11.000
One thing that I found is that people will ask how to do something

00:52:11.000 --> 00:52:15.000
and I will show them and maybe I'll spend half an hour or even more

00:52:15.000 --> 00:52:19.000
doing literally word for word what they ask for and then

00:52:19.000 --> 00:52:23.000
I'll give them this beautiful result. I'll be so proud of myself that we came up with this beautiful solution

00:52:23.000 --> 00:52:27.000
and they'll be like, no, that's not what it was.

00:52:27.000 --> 00:52:31.000
That's literally word for word what you asked for. They'll be like, yeah, but no, what I

00:52:31.000 --> 00:52:35.000
meant was this. Then I realized that I didn't really get what they really

00:52:35.000 --> 00:52:39.000
wanted. I think oftentimes in that relevance, what isn't really useful

00:52:39.000 --> 00:52:43.000
is if you can help the business is really asking them what you

00:52:43.000 --> 00:52:47.000
really want to do. Why do you need this number? What is really the goal?

00:52:47.000 --> 00:52:51.000
Maybe you can better help them really understand, okay, what are we going to do to have

00:52:51.000 --> 00:52:55.000
the really maximum ROI? That's something else that I really talk to my students about.

00:52:55.000 --> 00:52:59.000
What is the minimal thing, the easiest, smallest thing you can do

00:52:59.000 --> 00:53:03.000
that can have the greatest impact on your work and on your life and make things easier?

00:53:03.000 --> 00:53:07.000
Then focus on that, the 80-20 rule basically. Then they kind of

00:53:07.000 --> 00:53:11.000
start seeing things about it in a different way. Am I really doing something that's valuable?

00:53:11.000 --> 00:53:15.000
Is it really something that's going to have a huge ROI? Then they're a little bit more convinced

00:53:15.000 --> 00:53:19.000
to go about that. That's a lot of communication I find.

00:53:19.000 --> 00:53:23.000
I think that's a common theme that keeps coming up too

00:53:23.000 --> 00:53:27.000
is communication with the business. Understanding how to

00:53:27.000 --> 00:53:31.000
communicate so that it's relevant to them.

00:53:31.000 --> 00:53:35.000
I find that, at least for me, the objective is to make them feel

00:53:35.000 --> 00:53:39.000
ownership. If I can get that ownership where it's their baby

00:53:39.000 --> 00:53:43.000
and they care about the success or failure, that's the key.

00:53:43.000 --> 00:53:47.000
They're like, cool, it's your idea, then we're good.

